chapters.title: the silence from the universe was deafening

description:
The charity I strongly endorse is called ASRI. It’s a hospital in Borneo that provides affordable health care to villages on the edge of a national park in return for a pledge not to cut down trees, The pledges are monitored, and the result is a dramatic decrease in deforestation rates and an increase in the health of the local population. The founders are hoping to spread the idea to other countries. (see https://psmag.com/social-justice/save-the-trees-well-save-your-life-46121 for an explanation of their work.)

  You can make a donation by bank transfer here…
   http://www.alamsehatlestari.org/donate/

…or if you want to do it online they also have a US fundraising arm called Health in Harmony that is trying to get the project running in other countries:
 https://healthinharmony.org/donate/

SOURCES:

PragerU “Does Science argue for or against God?”
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UjGPHF5A6Po

S.E.T.I. mission: 
https://www.seti.org/

NASA’s three criteria for life:
https://www.nasa.gov/audience/forstudents/postsecondary/features/mars_life_feature_1015.html

Peter Schenkel article in Skeptical Inquirer:
https://www.csicop.org/si/show/seti_requires_a_skeptical_reappraisal

PragerU Frank Pastore video:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gIorXcloIac&t=74s

Further reading:
The research on quantum physics is now nearly 100 years old, so it has passed from journals into textbooks. I’ll spell these out so you can google them. There’s been a lot of updated research which you’ll find along the way, but so far no breakthrough that cures our current ignorance of the things I said “we don’t yet know” in the video:

Schrodinger’s Cat experiment
Double slit experiment (or Young’s slits)
Cosmic inflation theory
